================================================================================
Third-party components
================================================================================

1. mouse-forward-back  (vendored — src/mouse-forward-back/)
   The native X11 thumb-button hook is derived from "mouse-forward-back" by
   Justin Ostrander, used under the MIT License. The MIT license text is retained
   alongside the sources at src/mouse-forward-back/LICENSE.
   Upstream: https://github.com/jostrander/mouse-forward-back

2. vmd  (NOT redistributed)
   vinary-viewer enhances vmd (https://github.com/yoshuawuyts/vmd, MIT) by patching
   its installed npm package in place on the end user's own machine. vmd is neither
   bundled nor redistributed by this project; it must be installed separately
   (npm install -g vmd). The patches back up every file they touch and are reverted
   by uninstall.sh.

3. Spacemacs color palette  (inspiration)
   The bundled themes (src/themes/spacemacs-dark.css and spacemacs-light.css)
   reproduce the color *values* of the Spacemacs theme
   (https://github.com/nashamri/spacemacs-theme) so the previewer matches the
   Spacemacs editor. No Spacemacs source code is included.

4. github-markdown-css and highlight.js  (NOT redistributed)
   vmd supplies github-markdown-css and highlight.js. vinary-viewer's stylesheet
   overrides their appearance at runtime; it does not bundle either library.
